{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1502387634,"nonce":"k0XcsxwZJ4hSRgVfQ5bHdwEEbjM=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNDk0MjY4MTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1437","origin":"github"},"title":"Enhancement: Create new tool or modify BAM filter tools to remove header @ chroms in batch","message":"**Issue**: Mapping against genomes with many sequences (either from an unfinished assembly or a custom genome/transcriptome assembly) can create BAM files with very large headers. Even if the mapped results are filtered, this header remains. Having a large number of @ sequences causes many tools to fail for a memory error. MAC2 is one example. \n\n**Request** (one of the following):\n\n 1 - Update the \"Filter by region\" option on one or more of the BAM filter tools so that they accept a text file listing the regions (ideally just chrom IDs). One can enter in text for more than one region on the forms already, but 100+ is a long list and I am not sure how that would process (may run into another memory or other related error). It is tedious to enter anyway. A list is simple and can be parsed out of other results. Ideally, create a toggle to retain the simple text entry as \"enter regions\" but also add in a \"get regions from a list\" option to the tool forms.\n\n 2 - Create a tool that would reset the BAM header to only include @ lines for mapped data included in the filtered BAM dataset (only). This could be added to existing BAM filter tools as a new option - example: _Reset BAM header to only include reference genome regions represented by mapped data lines?_ Y/N where N is the default\n\n3 - Rejected idea: Create a tool that would reset a BAM header based on the contents of a reference fasta dataset. This is the least-best alternative for this use case. Users can already filter reference fasta datasets before mapping. But knowing what to keep before mapping/map quality filtering is .. circular analysis.","files":null}]}